{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Service Desk Cloud*. Using *JIRA Service Desk Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JSDSERVER-5289].
  {panel}
Currently, the {{Organizations}} field only support the following operators:
{code:java}
=, !=, in, not in{code}
It will be great if this field supports the following operators:
{code:java}
IS, IS NOT{code}
So that we can use JQL filter such as {{Organizations IS EMPTY}}.

h3. Summary

This request came from [DEVHELP-1952|https://ecosystem.atlassian.net/browse/DEVHELP-1952].

There was a change with the endpoint: /rest/servicedeskapi/latest/info and it now returns something like this:

{code}
{
   "version":"1234567890abcdefgh",
   "platformVersion":"1234567890abcdefgh",
   "buildDate":{
      "iso8601":"2018-11-20T18:00:00-0600",
      "jira":"2018-11-20T18:00:00.000-0600",
      "friendly":"Tuesday 6:00 PM",
      "epochMillis":1542758400000
   },
   "buildChangeSet":"1234567890abcdefgh",
   "isLicensedForUse":true,
   "_links":{
      "self":"https://<instance-name>.atlassian.net/rest/servicedeskapi/latest/info"
   }
}
{code}

It would be great if all Atlassian product's info requests told vendors what the platform they are talking to including Cloud, Server, Data Center.

At this time it's not possible to customize the payload which is sent on the Service Desk automation for Jira Cloud. On the Server Version we can customize and set some variables as shown on the doc that it follows:
{quote}
h5. [Jira Service Desk webhooks|https://developer.atlassian.com/server/jira/platform/jira-service-desk-webhooks/]
From Jira Service Desk Server 4.1, you can send a custom payload in your automation webhook.
{quote}

It would be nice to have this same option on Jira Cloud as well.
